Testing Plan: HOA Project Funding Content Pipeline Foundation
Context
We've built a complete automated content pipeline for www.hoaprojectfunding.com with 5 OpenClaw agents, configuration files, and automation scripts. Before enabling automated cron jobs, we need to thoroughly test every component to ensure:

Agents work correctly - Each agent can execute its core function (content generation, publishing, social media, email, engagement monitoring)
Configuration is complete - All required environment variables and config files are in place
Scripts function properly - Setup check, cron configuration, and cleanup scripts work as expected
Pipeline flows correctly - Content moves from generation ‚Üí approval ‚Üí publishing ‚Üí distribution ‚Üí engagement
Security is hardened - Exposed secrets are rotated, credentials are secured
The user wants to "TEST THE HECK OUT OF THIS" - so this plan provides comprehensive validation before going live with automation.

Phase 1: Pre-Testing Setup & Security Hardening
1.1 Run Setup Validation Script
Purpose: Identify what's missing before testing begins

Action:


cd /home/sjpilche/projects/openclaw-v1
bash scripts/quick-setup-check.sh
What to verify:

Script executes without errors
Identifies missing environment variables
Shows current agent registration status
Lists active (or missing) cron jobs
Displays pipeline readiness status
Expected output:

Color-coded ‚úÖ/‚ùå for each component
Prioritized next steps (üî¥ Critical, üü° High, üü¢ Low)
Pipeline status for: Content, Publishing, Social, Email, Engagement, Notifications
1.2 Security Hardening (CRITICAL)
Issues found in exploration:

OpenAI API key placeholder needs real key
JWT_SECRET needs rotation (currently exposed in conversation)
Default admin credentials need immediate change
Actions required:

File: server/.env.local

Update these variables:


# Rotate JWT secret
JWT_SECRET=<generate new 64-byte hex string>

# Set real OpenAI key
OPENAI_API_KEY=<real key from OpenAI dashboard>

# Change default admin credentials
DEFAULT_ADMIN_EMAIL=<your real email>
DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD=<strong password>
Generate new JWT secret:


node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
1.3 Configure Critical Environment Variables
File: server/.env.local

Add these REQUIRED variables:


# Telegram notifications (CRITICAL - needed for content review)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=<token from @BotFather>
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=<your chat ID>

# WordPress publishing (CRITICAL - can't publish without this)
WORDPRESS_URL=https://www.hoaprojectfunding.com
WORDPRESS_USER=<your WP username>
WORDPRESS_APP_PASSWORD=<WP application password>

# Email ESP (HIGH priority - needed for sequences)
SENDGRID_API_KEY=<SendGrid API key>
# OR
MAILCHIMP_API_KEY=<Mailchimp API key>

# Social media APIs (OPTIONAL - can post manually)
LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=<LinkedIn token>
FACEBOOK_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=<Facebook token>
How to get credentials:

Telegram bot: https://t.me/BotFather
WordPress app password: WP Admin ‚Üí Users ‚Üí Your Profile ‚Üí Application Passwords
SendGrid: https://sendgrid.com ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí API Keys
