# Email sequences config
cat workspaces/hoa-email-campaigns/config/sequences-config.json | jq .

# Lead scoring config
cat workspaces/hoa-social-engagement/config/lead-scoring.json | jq .
Expected: Both should parse without errors, showing formatted JSON

Validate structure:

sequences-config.json should have: application_abandonment, post_consult, monthly_newsletter
lead-scoring.json should have: high_intent_signals, medium_intent_signals, low_intent_signals, scoring thresholds
Phase 3: Individual Agent Testing (Manual Execution)
CRITICAL: Test each agent manually BEFORE enabling cron automation. This validates they work correctly and helps debug issues.

3.1 Test Content Writer Agent
Purpose: Generate a blog post from content calendar

Command:


openclaw agent \
  --agent hoa-content-writer \
  --local \
  --session-id "test-content-$(date +%s)" \
  --message "Pick the next unwritten topic from content-calendar.md. Generate a 1500-2000 word SEO-optimized blog post. Include two CTAs: one mid-article for the free consult, one end-of-article for the full application at www.hoaprojectfunding.com."
What to verify:

‚úÖ Agent completes without errors
‚úÖ Blog post saved to workspaces/hoa-content-writer/posts/drafts/YYYY-MM-DD-[topic].md
‚úÖ Post has frontmatter (title, description, slug, keywords, date)
‚úÖ Post has proper H1/H2/H3 structure
‚úÖ Post includes mid-article CTA (free consult)
‚úÖ Post includes end-of-article CTA (full application)
‚úÖ Post is 1500-2000 words
‚úÖ Telegram notification received (if configured)
Review generated content:


cat workspaces/hoa-content-writer/posts/drafts/*.md
Manual validation:

Content quality acceptable?
SEO metadata looks good?
CTAs properly formatted?
If successful: Move to approved for publishing test


mv workspaces/hoa-content-writer/posts/drafts/[filename].md \
   workspaces/hoa-content-writer/posts/approved/
3.2 Test CMS Publisher Agent
Purpose: Upload approved post to WordPress as draft

Prerequisites:

WordPress credentials configured in .env.local
Approved blog post exists from 3.1
Command:


openclaw agent \
  --agent hoa-cms-publisher \
  --local \
  --session-id "test-cms-$(date +%s)" \
  --message "Check approved directory and publish all approved posts to WordPress as drafts. Insert CTA blocks pointing to the application form and free consult at www.hoaprojectfunding.com."
What to verify:

‚úÖ Agent completes without errors
‚úÖ Post uploaded to WordPress as DRAFT status
‚úÖ CTA blocks inserted correctly
‚úÖ Featured image placeholder noted (manual step)
‚úÖ Telegram notification with WordPress draft link received
‚úÖ Post moved to published directory
‚úÖ Log file created in logs/
Manual WordPress check:

Log into WordPress admin
Go to Posts ‚Üí All Posts
Verify draft post exists
Check formatting, CTAs, content
If successful: Manually publish the post in WordPress to complete the test

