Would this be well-received in a group?
Does it provide genuine value?
No hard selling?
3.5 Test Social Engagement Monitor
Purpose: Monitor social platforms for engagement and score leads

Note: This requires actual social media activity to test properly. For now, test the agent runs without errors.

Command:


openclaw agent \
  --agent hoa-social-engagement \
  --local \
  --session-id "test-engagement-$(date +%s)" \
  --message "Check social platforms for new engagement. Score leads per lead-scoring.json. Draft responses for any leads scoring 10+. Include site link only for high-intent leads."
What to verify:

‚úÖ Agent completes without errors (even if no interactions found)
‚úÖ If no interactions: logs "No new engagement found" or similar
‚úÖ If interactions exist: drafts responses in workspaces/hoa-social-engagement/drafts/
‚úÖ Lead scoring applied correctly
‚úÖ HIGH-intent leads get CTA, MEDIUM-intent do not
‚úÖ Telegram digest sent
Manual validation:

Check if lead scoring.json thresholds make sense
Review any draft responses generated
