Success Criteria
The pipeline is ready for production when:

‚úÖ All agents execute without errors when triggered manually
‚úÖ Security issues addressed (secrets rotated, credentials secured)
‚úÖ All critical environment variables configured
‚úÖ Cron jobs configured and verified
‚úÖ End-to-end pipeline test successful (Monday ‚Üí Wednesday flow)
‚úÖ Telegram notifications working for content review
‚úÖ WordPress publishing working correctly
‚úÖ Social media posts generated in correct format
‚úÖ Lead scoring and engagement monitoring functional
‚úÖ First-week monitoring plan established
DO NOT enable cron automation until ALL success criteria met.

Rollback Plan (If Issues Arise)
If automation causes problems:

Immediate Actions:

# 1. Disable all cron jobs
openclaw cron list --json | jq -r '.[].id' | xargs -I {} openclaw cron remove --id {}

# 2. Verify removal
openclaw cron list

# 3. Continue manual execution while debugging
Debug Process:
Identify which agent/step failed
Review logs: openclaw logs --agent <agent-name>
Test agent manually with same message
Fix configuration issues
Re-test manually until working
Re-enable cron automation when stable
Post-Testing Documentation
After successful testing, document:

Any configuration changes made during testing
Lessons learned from agent behavior
Timing adjustments needed for cron schedule
Manual review process optimizations
Any additional environment variables needed
Common issues and solutions
Update these files:

README with actual test results
SKILL.md files with any clarifications
pipeline-schedule.md with timing adjustments
.env.local.example with all required variables
